Instruction encodings range between 1 and 10 bytes. An instruction consists of a 1-byte instruction specifier, possibly a 1-byte register specifier, and possibly an 8-byte constant word. Field £n specifies a particular integer operation (0Pg), data movement condition (cmovXX), or branch condition (jXX). All numeric values are shown in hexadecimal.
